%% Data Flow Diagram - Data Science Pipelines Operator
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Dashboard
    participant Router as OpenShift Router<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant API as DS Pipelines API Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTPS (pod-to-pod TLS)
    participant Argo as Argo Workflow Controller
    participant Pipeline as Pipeline Pod (executor)<br/>v2_component
    participant Persist as Persistence Agent
    participant MLMD as MLMD gRPC Server<br/>8080/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant Envoy as MLMD Envoy Proxy<br/>9090/TCP gRPC
    participant DB as MariaDB<br/>3306/TCP TLS
    participant S3 as S3 Object Store<br/>9000/443 TCP

    Note over User,S3: Flow 1: Pipeline Run Submission (External)
    User->>Router: POST /apis/v2beta1/runs<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Router->>Proxy: Reencrypt TLS<br/>Bearer Token
    Proxy->>Proxy: SubjectAccessReview<br/>OpenShift RBAC
    Proxy->>API: Forward to 8888/TCP<br/>pod-to-pod TLS (service-ca)
    API->>DB: Store pipeline run metadata<br/>MySQL TLS, Password auth
    API->>S3: Store pipeline spec artifact<br/>AccessKey/SecretKey
    API-->>Proxy: Run ID + status
    Proxy-->>Router: HTTPS response
    Router-->>User: JSON response

    Note over Argo,S3: Flow 2: Pipeline Execution (Argo Workflow)
    API->>Argo: Create Workflow CR<br/>via Kubernetes API 443/TCP
    Argo->>Pipeline: Schedule executor pod<br/>via K8s API
    Pipeline->>API: Report task status<br/>8888/TCP pod-to-pod TLS
    Pipeline->>MLMD: Log artifacts & executions<br/>8080/TCP gRPC TLS
    Pipeline->>S3: Upload/download artifacts<br/>AccessKey/SecretKey
    Persist->>API: Sync workflow status<br/>8888/TCP pod-to-pod TLS

    Note over User,DB: Flow 3: MLMD Metadata Query (External)
    User->>Router: gRPC metadata query<br/>HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    Router->>Proxy: Reencrypt TLS<br/>Bearer Token (SAR)
    Proxy->>Envoy: Forward to 9090/TCP<br/>gRPC TLS (service-ca)
    Envoy->>MLMD: Forward to 8080/TCP<br/>gRPC pod-to-pod TLS
    MLMD->>DB: Query metadata<br/>MySQL TLS, Password
    DB-->>MLMD: Results
    MLMD-->>Envoy: gRPC response
    Envoy-->>Proxy: gRPC response
    Proxy-->>Router: HTTPS
    Router-->>User: Metadata results

    Note over API,S3: Flow 4: Operator Reconciliation
    Note right of API: DSPO Controller checks<br/>health before deploying
    API->>DB: Health check (MySQL protocol)<br/>3306/TCP TLS
    API->>S3: Health check (S3 API)<br/>ListBuckets
